<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: OSLO; IN THE NAME OF PEACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Israel's Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin, Foreign Minister Shimon Peres and 
Palestine Liberation Organization Chairman Yasser Arafat will receive the Nobel 
Peace Prize on Saturday in the traditional awards ceremony at Oslo's city hall. 
</P>
<P>
 The three leaders will be honored for their work in fashioning the 
Israeli-Palestinian peace accord, which despite serious problems in its 
implementation has laid the basis for ending the Arab-Israeli conflict. 
</P>
<P>
 Prior to the ceremony, Rabin and Arafat will confer on the difficult steps 
they must take next in organizing the Palestinians' first national elections 
and pulling Israeli forces out of Palestinian towns and villages in the 
occupied West Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
