<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: CITY OF INDUSTRY; MAN 
KILLED BY DEPUTIES IN SHOOTOUT OUTSIDE BAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 24-year-old Upland man who apparently shot and wounded another man outside a 
bar early Monday morning was shot and killed by sheriff's deputies after he 
began firing at them, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, whose identity was not released because his relatives had not been 
notified, died outside the Fantasia nightclub at 17500 Castleton St. at 1:30 
a.m., sheriff's spokeswoman Britta Tubbs said. 
</P>
<P>
 The wounded man, Reginald Parker, 21, of Pomona, was in stable condition with 
a gunshot wound to his buttocks, Tubbs said. Several disturbances had been 
reported that night at the club and the management had agreed to shut down an 
hour early at 1 a.m. to prevent other problems, Tubbs said. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies were helping to escort about 300 patrons outside when a fistfight 
broke out in front of the club, Tubbs said. 
</P>
<P>
 While breaking up the fight, deputies heard gunfire from the parking lot. As 
they began searching for the source, one deputy saw a man armed with a 
semiautomatic handgun shoot another man lying on the ground, Tubbs said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man then turned toward the deputies, pointed his gun at them and began 
shooting, Tubbs said. Four deputies returned fire with 9-millimeter handguns, 
striking the man several times in the upper torso. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA120694-0051 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 105274 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
December 6, 1994, Tuesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
