<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OJAI; CAMPFIRE BAN LIFTED IN NATIONAL FOREST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Restrictions on campfires in Los Padres National Forest have been lifted 
because of cooler weather and the beginning of the rainy season. 
</P>
<P>
 Wood-burning campfires will now be allowed outside of developed campgrounds 
for those carrying permits. Permits may be obtained at the Ojai Ranger Station, 
1190 E. Ojai Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire restrictions are imposed each summer to reduce the chance of 
wildfires, then lifted each fall when the weather increases the moisture level 
in vegetation. 
</P>
<P>
 The forest service also will allow residents living inside Los Padres National 
Forest to burn their yard debris. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
