274 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP; THOUSAND OAKS' BUZ GREENE A 1-STROKE WINNER IN TOURNEY OF CLUB 
CHAMPIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANA HADDAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Buz Greene of Thousand Oaks fired a one-under-par 71 Monday to win the 
Southern California Golf Assn.'s 20th Tournament of Club Champions at North 
Ranch Country Club in Westlake Village. 
</P>
<P>
 Greene, club champion at Saticoy Country Club near Camarillo, held off John 
Wardrup (Torrey Pines) by one shot. 
</P>
<P>
 The event pitted 95 individual men's club champions from throughout the 
Southland. Gary Klahn of Agoura and Lee Davis of Thousand Oaks finished in a 
four-way tie for third at 73. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Port of Chatsworth and Bill O'Connor, club champion at North Ranch, 
finished in a tie for seventh at two-over 74. Former Cal State Northridge 
standout Rick Sessinghaus tied for 13th with a 75. Girls' Tennis 
</P>
<P>
 Second-seeded Julia Feldman of Taft High advanced to the semifinals of the 
City Section girls' individual tennis tourney with a 6-4, 6-1 win over Leslie 
Musser of Van Nuys at the Racquet Centre Monday in Studio City. 
</P>
<P>
 Feldman, a senior who is 46-2 over three seasons, said she was tired from 
playing three matches in a juniors tournament last weekend and didn't get 
warmed up until the second set. 
</P>
<P>
 Feldman will face Ilona Kordanskay of Los Angeles High in Wednesday's 
semifinals. Kordanskay has won all three of her matches in the tournament by 
6-0, 6-0 scores. She was ranked 53rd in the 14-and-under division by the 
Southern California Tennis Assn. last year. 
</P>
<P>
 In quarterfinal doubles matches, Stephanie Shapiro and Terri Rosenthal of Taft 
defeated Alison Fischer and Jennie Wilson of Palisades, 3-6, 6-2, 6-4. Carolyn 
Lee and Brenda Moore of Palisades defeated Taft's Ravid Levy and Alicia Whelan, 
7-5, 5-7, 7-6 (8-6). DANA HADDAD 
</P>
