<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES: SITES, DATES FOR FOOTBALL GAMES SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE TERRY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The date of the Southern Section Division V football championship game between 
Newport Harbor and Servite has been changed to Friday and will be played at 
Orange Coast College, the section announced. Kickoff is 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The site of Saturday's Division X final between Orange Lutheran and Van Nuys 
Montclair Prep will be Los Angeles Valley College. 
</P>
<P>
 Bishop Amat, the nation's top-ranked team, plays host to Mater Dei on Saturday 
at Anaheim Stadium in the Division I title game. Kickoff is 7:40 p.m., and the 
game will be televised by KCOP Channel 13. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are on sale at the participating schools this week and at the stadiums 
on game day. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills' Brendan McGraw gained 100 yards in Saturday's 34-21 loss to 
Colton Bloomington in the Division VIII semifinals to give him 2,511 yards for 
the season and the county rushing title by 11 yards over Costa Mesa's Charles 
Chatman. McGraw's total was short of Jeff Byrd's county record of 2,596 yards 
set in 1992 at Rancho Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
 McGraw also scored a touchdown Saturday, giving him 42, adding to his 
single-season county record. 
</P>
<P>
 "He didn't care about individual goals; he was concerned about the team 
winning and not winning," Laguna Hills Coach Steve Bresnahan said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He'll appreciate much later what he did, but he knows he had some pretty good 
linemen blocking for him. . . . It will be a long-term reward, but he's 
disappointed he's not still playing." MIKE TERRY 
</P>
</TEXT>
