GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; ALISO NIGUEL SETS MARK IN 52-28 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Aliso Niguel set a school single-game rebounding record with 55 Monday as the 
Wolverines beat Pacifica, 52-28, in a University girls' basketball tournament 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 The previous mark was 41. Deana Mitchelson and Brook Hyman combined for 45 of 
the rebounds, with Mitchelson getting 23 and Hyman grabbing 22. 
</P>
<P>
 Mitchelson also finished with a game-high 30 points. Hyman added 11 for Aliso 
Niguel (2-1). For Pacifica, Erin Kiyomura scored more than half of the Mariners 
points with 17, making 13 of 16 free throws. 
</P>
