<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAGELLAN TO HAVE NO DIVIDEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fidelity Investments said Monday that it will not distribute year-end 
dividends for its Magellan Fund, the largest mutual fund in the country. 
</P>
<P>
 Company analysts had predicted in November that the fund would distribute 
$4.32 per share on the $37.6 billion fund, which has about 3 million 
shareholders. 
</P>
<P>
 Company officials said a calculation error is responsible for the revision and 
that it is not a reflection of the performance of the stock and bond markets, 
which have languished through much of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 "In the normal recalculation, we uncovered an error which meant no year-end 
distribution," Fidelity spokeswoman Jane Jamieson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
