<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: BENNER TO HANDLE FLUOR INFORMATION SYSTEMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dennis W. Benner has been appointed to the newly created position of vice 
president and chief information officer for Fluor Corp., the Irvine-based 
engineering, construction and diversified services company. He will be 
responsible for the company's information systems, including hardware, 
software, network and telecommunications activities. Before joining Fluor, 
Benner was vice president and general manager of TRW's Information Technology 
Services division in Orange. Before that, he was division vice president of 
marketing for Automatic Data Processing Inc. in La Palma. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ken Treaster has joined Interior Specialists, a design center specializing 
in residential flooring and window coverings, as president of the Orange County 
division in Irvine. Treaster was formerly senior vice president of sales and 
marketing for Tuftex Carpet Mills in Santa Fe Springs and, before that, 
regional vice president of sales and marketing for Shaw Industries, a carpet 
manufacturer. 
</P>
<P>
 * Brad Fanshaw has been appointed president of Coddington Cos., a Stanton 
hot-rod and custom wheel company. Fanshaw, who has been with the company for 
four years, had been vice president and director of marketing. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jo-Ann Moberly has joined Mariners Bank in San Clemente as vice president 
and operations administrator. She had been vice president and operations 
manager at the Newport Beach office of City National Bank for the past nine 
years. Before that, Moberly was a banking instructor in the Regional 
Occupational Program.  
</P>
<P>
 * John D. Jones has been appointed director of contracting and compliance for 
Prescription Solutions, the pharmacy benefit management subsidiary of 
PacifiCare Health Systems Inc. in Cypress. Before joining the company, Jones 
was director of pharmacy at Blue Shield of California. 
</P>
<P>
 * Robert Grambo and Greg Hawkins have been selected to head the U.S. sales 
division of Ingram Micro Inc., a Santa Ana wholesale distributor of 
microcomputer products. They succeed Jim Wittrey, who left the company. Grambo 
is vice president of telesales, and Hawkins is vice president of sales. 
</P>
<P>
 * Katie Milius has been promoted to manager of corporate team relations for 
National Telephone & Communications Co. in Irvine. Milius, who joined the 
company in 1991, had been corporate team administrator.  
</P>
<P>
 * John Hirabayashi has joined the Hyatt Regency Irvine as senior sales 
manager, responsible for financial, real estate, restaurant and food product 
accounts. He was formerly national sales manager at the Sheraton Grande in Los 
Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 * Lou Ferrini has been appointed vice president of sales for Olicon Imaging 
Systems Inc., a San Clemente medical-imaging company. Previously, he was 
national sales manager for Biomagnetic Technology Inc. Ferrini has also held 
executive sales positions at Picker International Inc. and Adac Laboratories 
Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 * Michael J. Occhipinti has been appointed vice president of planned giving 
for Saddleback Memorial Foundation, the fund-raising arm of Saddleback Memorial 
Medical Center in Laguna Hills. He formerly was a charitable gift planner for 
the Salvation Army in Southern California for the Western United States. 
</P>
<P>
 * Alan E. Ross has been selected chairman of the Semiconductor Industry Assn. 
Ross is president of Rockwell Telecommunications in Newport Beach.  
</P>
<P>
 * Richard C. Tippett has joined CalComp, an Anaheim maker of computer graphics 
products, as vice president for manufacturing. He succeeds John W. Powell, who 
left the company. Tippett was formerly president and general manager of Four Pi 
Systems, a San Diego subsidiary of Hewlett-Packard. Before that, he was with 
GenRad Inc. for nine years and with NCR Corp. for ten years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
