<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Noah Culp 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza, Junior 
</P>
<P>
 Wrestling/145 pounds 
</P>
<P>
 Last season, wrestling at 140 pounds, Culp had a 15-19 record. This season, he 
has turned things around early. Saturday, he won the 145-pound title at the 
32-team El Dorado Holiday tournament.He beat Loara's Richard Meza, ranked No. 1 
in the county in the preseason poll, 9-0, in the semifinals and pinned Poway's 
Mike Koelzer in the final. Culp also pinned his opponent in 33 seconds in the 
Aztecs' 40-11 victory over El Dorado earlier in the week. It was Esperanza's 
second victory over the Golden Hawks in the 22-year history of the series. 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 Tyler Kalklosch 
</P>
<P>
 * Mission Viejo, junior. Made a 55-foot shot with 1.9 seconds left to send the 
title game of the Mission Viejo tournament into overtime. Scored 18 points in 
the Diablos' 77-73 victory over Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
 Cory Johnson 
</P>
<P>
 * Los Alamitos, junior. Scored 22 points in the Griffins' 72-53 victory over 
Corona del Mar in the title game of the Daily Pilot Tip-Off Classic. 
</P>
<P>
 Football 
</P>
<P>
 David Bedard 
</P>
<P>
 * Servite, senior. Rushed for 168 yards and three touchdowns in the Friars' 
34-19 victory over El Toro in a Division V semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
 John Flynn 
</P>
<P>
 * Mater Dei, senior. Rushed for 58 yards, passed for 82 yards and two 
touchdowns, including the 11-yard game-winner to Casey Rouintree with 43 
seconds left in the Monarchs' 28-24 Division I victory over Los Alamitos. 
</P>
