ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Misty May 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor, Senior 
</P>
<P>
 Volleyball/Outside hitter 
</P>
<P>
 Few people knew it, but May was feeling ill during the Sailors' State Division 
I title match with Stockton St. Mary's Saturday. It didn't show.She had 21 
kills and 10 digs in a 15-4, 16-14, 15-10 victory. "Misty wasn't feeling well 
but she still had a great match," Newport Harbor Coach Dan Glenn said. "I think 
she has played the best she has ever played in our run in the playoffs." May 
had 15 kills and 10 digs in a sweep of Santa Cruz Harbor in the semifinals. 
