</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Teachers in the Garden Grove Unified School District have received almost 
$8,500 in grants through the Disneyland Fine Arts Partnership Program, a 
district spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Forty-one teachers will share the grants, which help pay for projects and 
materials designed to involve children in visual and performing arts, said 
spokesman Alan Trudell. 
</P>
<P>
 Teachers will use the grants to pay for field trips to the Bowers Museum in 
Santa Ana, for computer hardware to create animated videos and for professional 
choreographers for a dance class, Trudell said. 
</P>
<P>
 The awards are distributed twice a year. Teachers districtwide won about 
$8,200 during the last round of grants, Trudell said. JON NALICK 
