<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: VILLA PARK; CITY TO CONSIDER LAWS ON TRASH, EYESORES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council will soon consider toughening laws on property maintenance. 
</P>
<P>
 Proposed changes in the law would allow fines for broken and unused machinery 
sitting on property and broken windows that are not promptly repaired. 
</P>
<P>
 Another change would prohibit trash storage in front or side yards if visible 
from public streets. Trash and garbage also could not be stored in areas that 
are deemed public right of ways. 
</P>
<P>
 No date has yet been set for consideration of these changes, which City 
Manager Fred Maley has told the council he will propose soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
