<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; RESTAURANTS EXCHANGE TOYS FOR REBATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM RAGAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bring in a toy and get a meal at a reduced price. 
</P>
<P>
 That's what three El Torito Grills in Newport Beach, Costa Mesa and Irvine are 
offering for the holidays in conjunction with Share Our Selves, a nonprofit 
charitable organization. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the program, anyone who brings an unwrapped toy to any of the 
restaurants will receive a certificate for $10 off on any meal check that 
exceeds $25. The toys will then be given to SOS and distributed to 
underprivileged children. 
</P>
<P>
 "Share Our Selves does a tremendous job of helping brighten the holidays for 
many needy families in our own back yard," said Jerry Frye, district manager 
for the restaurants. 
</P>
<P>
 "We thought assisting them in the toy department would be great, and we 
believe our guests will enjoy participating too. The certificates are our way 
of thanking them for their involvement." 
</P>
<P>
 The toy drive, which started last week, will continue until Dec. 20. The 
certificates will be valid through Jan. 15. TOM RAGAN 
</P>
