<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LA PALMA; APPLICANTS SOUGHT FOR ADVISORY PANELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Applicants are sought for 12 vacancies on citizen advisory committees in the 
city. 
</P>
<P>
 There are eight openings on the Cultural and Beautification Committee, three 
openings on the Traffic Safety Committee and one on the Development Committee. 
</P>
<P>
 The Development Committee meets at 7:30 p.m. on the second Monday of every 
other month, beginning in January. Members review proposed subdivisions and 
commercial structures. City Clerk Brigitte Charles said desirable 
qualifications include an ability to read landscaping plans and working 
drawings and some knowledge of municipal government. Members are paid $25 per 
meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 The other openings are unpaid. The Cultural and Beautification Committee meets 
at 5 p.m. on the second Tuesday of every month. Charles said applicants should 
have an interest in promoting culture and arts. 
</P>
<P>
 The Traffic Safety Committee meetings are held at 6 p.m. on the second Tuesday 
of January, April, July and October. Charles said that applicants should, 
preferably, have a knowledge of traffic and safety laws as they pertain to 
development. 
</P>
<P>
 All applicants must be residents of the city. The deadline for applications is 
Dec. 27. For more information, call (714) 523-7700.BILL BILLITER 
</P>
