<P>
SADDLEBACK PAPER MAKES COLLEGE TOP 5 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback College's newspaper, The Lariat, has been judged one of the 
nation's top five community college newspapers. 
</P>
<P>
 The publication received the honor from the Associated College Press during 
the organization's annual conference Nov. 6 in New Orleans. The Lariat received 
the National Pacemaker award. The newspaper also won the award in 1989. 
</P>
<P>
 The award is given for general excellence and was based on five issues of The 
Lariat published during the 1993-94 academic year. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to being honored with the award, The Lariat was inducted into the 
Associated College Press Hall of Fame, in recognition of 10 consecutive 
semesters of publishing excellence. 
</P>
