<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: OROAMERICA INC.'S EARNINGS RISE IN THIRD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 OroAmerica Inc., a Burbank supplier of gold jewelry, reported that its fiscal 
third-quarter earnings rose by half over a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 In the three months ended Oct. 28, OroAmerica had a profit of $2.21 million, 
up 51% from its $1.47 million in earnings in the same quarter last year. Its 
net sales inched up 4%, to $64.6 million, from $62.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's results for the third quarter a year ago included a $564,000 
one-time charge from the early payment of debt. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months ended Oct. 28, the company's net income fell 38%, to $2.98 
million from $4.79 million. Net sales were $151.6 million, up 8% from $141 
million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
