<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: ELTRON PURCHASES BRITISH BAR-CODE FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eltron International Inc., a Chatsworth maker of bar-code label printers and 
software, said it has purchased about $1.2 million in assets and the 
distribution business of a British distributor of bar-code and ticket printing 
equipment. 
</P>
<P>
 Eltron said it paid $360,000 in cash and assumed $880,000 in trade liabilities 
and debt in its deal with Russet Ltd. It said it believes that Russet can add 
about $3 million to its 1995 revenues. 
</P>
<P>
 Russet will continue to operate under its current name, and will serve as a 
base for distributing bar-code equipment within the United Kingdom and as a 
manufacturing base and distributor for other products throughout Europe, Eltron 
said. 
</P>
