<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW / JACK SEARLES: EMPLOYERS ARE REPORTED UPBEAT ABOUT 
HIRING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County employers are upbeat about their hiring plans for the first 
quarter of 1995, according to a quarterly survey by Manpower Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 Increased staffing is expected by 27% of the county's companies, while 7% plan 
cutbacks, the study shows. The rest of the firms are unsure or plan no changes. 
</P>
<P>
 Three months ago, Manpower found that 17% of the county's large employers 
planned to increase payrolls and 3% expected layoffs. A year ago, 13% predicted 
increased hiring and 13% forecast decreases. 
</P>
<P>
 Hiring prospects in the county will be brightest this winter in manufacturing, 
transportation, public utilities, wholesaling and retailing, the survey showed. 
Layoffs are expected in health care and other service fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
