<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: TRAVEL AND TOURISM; JOHN WAYNE AIRPORT IN GOOD CHEER WITH CHILDREN'S 
ART SHOW, HOLIDAY FEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Chris Woodyard, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The holiday spirit is evident across Orange County, from the Ritz Carlton, 
seasonably chic, to Disneyland, with its daily Christmas parade, and, of 
course, John Wayne Airport. 
</P>
<P>
 John Wayne Airport? Yes.On Sunday, the airport will deck its halls with 
children's artwork. The "Flights of Fancy" exhibit will include 89 works 
selected from 1,340 entries. 
</P>
<P>
 Dance groups and high school and college choral groups will perform in the 
food court of the main terminal, as well as stroll about. 
</P>
<P>
 "I hope that not only those traveling through John Wayne Airport this holiday 
season, but all members of our community, will come to enjoy and share in the 
holiday spirit," Airport Director Janice Mittermeier said. 
</P>
<P>
 The holiday festival at the airport through Jan. 15 will include 14 
performance groups. They include mariachis, a singing harpist, ballet 
folklorico, a barbershop quartet and brass bands. 
</P>
