<P>
118 FREEWAY NAMED AFTER RONALD REAGAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With fond words for the nation's 40th President, the state Senate on Monday 
overwhelmingly approved designating the Simi Valley-San Fernando Valley Freeway 
as the Ronald Reagan Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 On the first day of the 1995-96 legislative session, the Senate voted 38 to 0 
to re-christen the entire length of the freeway, California 118, in honor of 
the two-term President from the state. 
</P>
<P>
 State Sen. Cathie Wright (R-Simi Valley), a co-author of the resolution along 
with Senate President Pro Tem Bill Lockyer (D-Hayward), had urged colleagues to 
approve the action, in part because the freeway leads to the Ronald Reagan 
Presidential Library in Simi Valley. 
</P>
